
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Privacy_policy";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}
@section Styles {
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/Content/about.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/Content/style.css">
}
<section class="about-us-section">
    <div class="about-content">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>
            EventGate is committed to protecting your personal information and ensuring a safe and transparent user experience.
            This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and how we safeguard your information while you
            use our platform.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
            We may collect personal details such as your name, email address, phone number, location, and ticket purchase history.
            Additionally, we gather usage data including IP address, browser information, device type, and cookies for improving
            our website performance.
        </p>

        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Management:</strong> Creating and managing your EventGate account.</li>
            <li><strong>Ticket Processing:</strong> Completing purchases, sending confirmations, and providing event access.</li>
            <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Sending updates, notifications, and customer support messages.</li>
            <li><strong>Platform Improvement:</strong> Enhancing user experience and recommending relevant events.</li>
            <li><strong>Security:</strong> Preventing fraudulent activities and ensuring system safety.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cookies & Tracking</h2>
        <p>
            We use cookies to personalize your experience, remember your preferences, and analyze website traffic. You may disable
            cookies through your browser settings, but some features may not function properly without them.
        </p>

        <h2>Information Sharing</h2>
        <p>
            EventGate does not sell or rent your personal data. Your information may be shared only with trusted service providers
            (payment processors, email services, analytics tools) or if required by law. When you purchase a ticket, necessary details
            may be provided to event organizers for entry and verification purposes.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>
            Your data is stored on secure servers and protected with industry-standard security measures against unauthorized
            access, alteration, or disclosure.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
            You may request access to your personal information, ask for corrections, or request data deletion at any time.
            You can also opt out of marketing communications.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
            For any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
            <strong>support@eventgate.com</strong>.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>


